
Use #!hashbang line to wrap a script to another
'''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''

See the the behavior of these by executing
(after checking all files here look OK):

1$ ./inner-no-args.sh
2$ ./inner-w-arg.sh

3$ ./inner-no-args.sh cmd line args 4 5 6
4$ ./inner-w-arg.sh cmd line args 4 5 6
